{
  "message": "fix(decoding): add K..K' zero-padding rows to decode_block\n\nThe decoder's decode_block function was missing the zero-padded rows for\nESIs K..K' that the encoder implicitly adds. When K < K' (always true since\nthe RFC 6330 systematic index table rounds up), the constraint matrix has\nL = K'+S+H columns but the decoder only provided S+H+received_symbols rows,\nwhich is fewer than L for small K values (e.g. k=2 maps to K'=10, L=27).\n\nThis caused InsufficientSymbols errors in pipeline roundtrip tests even when\nall source+repair symbols were correctly received.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
